description:
Core benchmark infrastructure - runner, metrics, cost tracking, reporting.

## Files
- tests/benchmarks/framework/types.ts - BenchmarkMetrics, CostMetrics interfaces
- tests/benchmarks/framework/runner.ts - BenchmarkRunner with warmup/iterations
- tests/benchmarks/framework/metrics.ts - MetricCollector, aggregation (p50/p95/p99)
- tests/benchmarks/framework/cost-tracker.ts - DO billing cost estimation
- tests/benchmarks/framework/reporter.ts - Console, JSON, markdown output

## Key Types
```typescript
interface BenchmarkMetrics {
  latency: { p50, p95, p99, max, min, avg: number }
  throughput: { opsPerSecond, bytesPerSecond: number }
  cost: { rowWrites, rowReads, storageGb, cpuMs, estimatedCost: number }
  resources: { peakMemoryMb, storageBytesUsed: number }
  context: { store, operation, datasetSize, iterations, environment }
}
```

## RED Tests
- BenchmarkRunner executes with warmup
- MetricCollector computes percentiles correctly
- CostTracker intercepts SQLite operations
- Reporter generates markdown tables

Create schema extension API that wraps ai-database:

```typescript
import { DB } from '@dotdo/core'

// Use ai-database syntax
const schema = DB({
  Customer: {
    name: 'string',
    '-> orders': 'Order[]',
    '<~ industry': 'Industry',
  }
})

// Extend DO with schema
class MyDO extends DO.with(schema) { }
```

Also support:
- Zod schemas
- Direct Drizzle schemas for escape hatch

